Sentencas: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) were fabricated depositing proton conducting BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x (BCY10) thick films on cermet substrates made of nickel oxide-yttrium doped barium cerate (NiO-BCY10) using electrophoretic deposition (EPD) technique.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: The influence of the EPD parameters on the microstructure and electrical properties of BCY10 thick films was investigated.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: Deposited BCY10 thick films together with green anode substrates were co-sintered in a single heating treatment at 1,550 degrees C for 2 h to obtain dense electrolyte and suitably porous anodes.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: The half-cells were characterised by field emission scanning electron microscopy (FE-SEM) and by X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: A composite cathode specifically developed for BCY electrolytes, made of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3(LSCF, mixed oxygen-ion/electronic conductor) and BaCe0.9Yb0.1O3-delta (10YbBC, mixed protonic/electronic conductor), was used.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: Fuel cells were prepared by slurry coating the composite cathode on the co-sintered half-cells.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: Fuel cell tests and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) were performed in the 550-700 degrees C temperature range.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 296 mW cm(-2) was achieved at 700 degrees C for electrolyte deposited at 60 V for 1 min.
Titulo: Anode Supported Protonic Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated Using Electrophoretic Deposition
